title: Veronica Roth-Allegiant.mp3
description: The background to the story, revealed in the first novel of the trilogy, explains how a ruined Chicago in the near future is divided into five separate factions. They are Abnegation, meant to uphold selflessness, Amity, meant to uphold peacefulness, Candor, meant to uphold honesty, Dauntless, meant to uphold bravery, and Erudite, meant to uphold knowledge. Tris is tested with equal aptitude for Abnegation, Erudite, and Dauntless, three different factions. This classifies her as "Divergent" and she is warned never to share this information with anyone for fear of her life. Those who are Divergent are hunted and killed by the ruthless leader of Erudite, and those who fail the initiation of their particular faction are deemed factionless
